## 🚀 Project Overview
**Smart ECG Analyzer & Heart Risk Predictor** is a health-tech project aiming to:
- 📄 **Read & analyze ECGs** from PDF reports  
- 🖼 **Extract ECG data from images/photos** using OCR  
- 🧠 **Predict possible heart risks** using AI  
- 🩺 **Give health recommendations** for prevention  

💡 **Goal:** Make preventive heart care accessible with AI-driven insights.

---

## ✨ Features
✅ PDF ECG Upload → Automatic extraction & analysis  
✅ Image ECG Upload → OCR-based recognition  
✅ AI Model → Predict abnormalities & risks  
✅ Patient Data Form → Combine ECG + health info  
✅ Recommendations → Lifestyle & care tips  
✅ Web App Interface → Easy to use for doctors & patients  

---

## 🛠 Tech Stack
| Category | Tools / Frameworks |
|----------|---------------------|
| **Languages** | Python |
| **Frameworks** | Streamlit / Flask |
| **ML Libraries** | scikit-learn, TensorFlow, PyTorch |
| **Data Processing** | Pandas, NumPy |
| **PDF Handling** | PyMuPDF |
| **OCR** | Pytesseract |
| **Design** | Figma |
| **Version Control** | GitHub |

---

## 📍 Roadmap

### Phase 1: 📑 Research & Setup  
- Define scope & requirements  
- Collect ECG datasets  
- Create team roles  

### Phase 2: 🖥 Development  
- PDF ECG extraction  
- Image ECG OCR  
- ML model for heart risk prediction  
- Patient data integration  

### Phase 3: 🧠 AI Intelligence  
- Model accuracy improvements  
- Recommendation engine  
- PDF result export  

### Phase 4: 🌐 UI & Deployment  
- Build user-friendly web interface  
- Cloud deployment  
- Final testing with real data  

